contentrichtext.text: {{wiktionary|HM|hm|.hm}} '''HM''' may refer to: * [[HM (magazine)]], a Christian hard rock magazine * [[Henry Molaison]], previously known as patient H.M., a man with anterograde amnesia * HM, the IATA airline code for [[Air Seychelles]] * HM, the ISO 3166 digram and FIPS PUB 10-4 territory code of [[Heard Island and McDonald Islands]] * H.M., postnominal initials of the [[Sisters of the Holy Humility of Mary]] * [[H&M]] (originally Hennes & Mauritz), a Swedish clothing company '''HM''' may stand for: * His/Her [[Majesty]], a form of address for a monarch or queen consort * [[Hidden Machine]], in the video game series Pokémon * [[Hindley–Milner]], a type system * [[Hennessy–Milner logic]], a modal logic * Logo of [[Hindustan Motors]], an automobile manufacturer of India * [[Hospital Corpsman]], in the United States Navy '''hm''' may refer to: * [[hamburgmuseum]], the name of a history museum in Hamburg, Germany * [[hectometre]], an SI unit of length {{disambiguation}}
